date: July 2009 Texas is one of the seven states of the United States with no personal state income tax. In addition, Texas does not allow any lower level of government (counties, cities, etc.) to impose an income tax. This means that, for the residents of Texas, the maximum rate of income taxation is the top rate set by the US Government.  Businesses, except for sole proprietorships and partnerships, are subject to a gross margins tax. |
